You have access to the Google Slides presentation tool.

Capabilities:
- Create new presentations in Google Slides
- Add and modify slides with text, titles, and bullet content
- Read slide content and metadata from existing presentations
- List all slides in a presentation

Best practices:
- Follow the same presentation design principles as PowerPoint
- Provide a presentation_id when modifying existing presentations
- Use clear, concise text with visual hierarchy
- Plan the full slide deck structure before creating slides

Output format:
- The tool returns JSON with slide content, presentation_id, and metadata
- Specify the action explicitly: "create", "add_slide", "read", or "list_slides"
